thread.title_full: Mateen Cleaves investigated in sexual assault case - UPI.com

author: upi.com
title: Mateen Cleaves investigated in sexual assault case
text:
| License Photo Former Michigan State standout Mateen Cleaves was named in a sexual assault investigation in Michigan but has not been charged.
The case was transferred to Detroit from Genesee County because of a potential conflict of interest with the prosecutor, the Flint Journal reported Friday.
No information about of the case, which remains under investigation, were available. Cleaves ' attorney, Frank Manley, told the newspaper that the details of the complaint were private.
Cleaves, a Flint native, helped lead Michigan State to the NCAA title in 2000 before playing in the NBA. He is now a television analyst.
